<LegalLayout title="Support" appName="SnipSnaps">
  <p>SnipSnaps helps you clean up your photo library through quick review sessions.</p>

  <h2>Why does SnipSnaps ask for Photos access?</h2>
  <p>
    SnipSnaps needs Photos access to show your library for review and to delete only the photos
    you select.
  </p>

  <h2>Does SnipSnaps upload my photos?</h2>
  <p>No. Photo review happens on device.</p>

  <h2>Where do deleted photos go?</h2>
  <p>
    Deleted photos are moved to Recently Deleted by iOS. You can recover them from the Photos
    app until iOS permanently removes them.
  </p>

  <h2>Can I use limited Photos access?</h2>
  <p>Yes. With limited access, SnipSnaps can review only the photos you have allowed.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For help with SnipSnaps, contact Kyter, LLC at
    <a href="mailto:dev@kyter.com">dev@kyter.com</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
